docs.abstract: State officials across United States report they have found very few credible allegations of voter fraud in 2016 presidential election, with no state reporting indications of widespread fraud; findings clearly refute Pres-elect Donald Trump's claims that millions of illegal voters backed Hillary Clinton; experts say threat of voter fraud has proven to be minuscule problem but potent political weapon.

headline.main: All This Talk of Voter Fraud? Across U.S., Officials Found Next to None
